;

VARIABLE LEVERDAN
VARIABLE SHINLOCK
VARIABLE SHINBOOM

NUMBER 772
NAME Mitchell's grove

*DESCRIPTION_START
You stand before a tumbling cascade of clear mountain water, a mist-enshrouded
waterfall whose dull, gentle roar mutes the sounds of the surrounding forest.
A grove of ancient white pines stands somber guard at the end of this mountain
glen, their castaway needles forming a rich carpet of dry, soft orange. The
falls empty into a shallow pool whose surface changes from the cacophonic
impact of the falling liquid to the calm, cool mirror of its outer edges.
*DESCRIPTION_END

FOREST

EXIT S 605

IFPREVERB EAST -1
        IFVAR FLAG3 = 33
                IFVAR FLAG2 = 22
                        CLEARVERB
                        IFVAR SHINLOCK = 1
                                ECHO PLAYER You swim east under the falls and through the arch.
                                ECHO OTHERS %N swims under the falls and out of sight.
				DISBAND
                                MOVE 773
                                AFFECT 773
                                ECHO OTHERS %N arrives through the arch, %h watery form quickly drying to normalcy.
                        ENDIF
                        IFVAR SHINLOCK = 0
                                ECHO PLAYER You swim east under the falls, only to discover that the arch is nothing but a painted shape on the stone behind them.
                                ECHO OTHERS %N swims east under the falls, then comes back up to the surface.
                        ENDIF
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
ENDIF

ITEM 0 229 ADJ1=347 ADJ2=234
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The trees stand tall and strong, resistant to the mountain winds and the
falling rain, the blistering sun and the encroachment of boring beetles. In
the trunk of one of the largest pines you see a carved heart with the
names Meandre and Tordant inscribed therein.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GO 0
        CLEARVERB
        DISBAND
	ECHO OTHERS %N walks into the stand of pine trees.
        ECHO PLAYER You walk among the pine trees, looking skyward along the length of their dry, white trunks.
ENDIF

