NUMBER 2365
NAME Through passage
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS

*DESCRIPTION_START
This simple connecting passage has one distinguishing feature, a huge, heavy
iron lever. The walls flicker with shadows and light, but the lever sits
there, solid as anything, just begging to be pulled.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB SEARCH -1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER A quick search shows you a switch on one wall. How delightful!
ENDIF

ITEM 0 641
EXTEND 0 set into one wall
IFPREVERB PULL 0
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR LEVERDAN = 1
                ECHO PLAYER It won't move.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR LEVERDAN = 0
                EQUAL LEVERDAN 1
                ECHO PLAYER You pull on the lever, which comes down, then immediately slides back up.
                ECHO OTHERS %N pulls on the lever, which comes down, then immediately slides back up.
                PLREVENT 1
                CONTPLREVENT
                ECHO ALL You hear a "CLANK!" sound, then a whirring.
                PLREVENT 2
                CONTPLREVENT
                ECHO ALL The lever shudders slightly as the ceiling descends in pieces, slamming down...
                DAMAGEALL CRUSH 140 %N is slammed!
                PLREVENT 1
                CONTPLREVENT
                ECHO ALL The ceiling retracts.
                EQUAL LEVERDAN 0
        ENDIF
ENDIF

